    "narrative": "The Austin Waves' offensive core is anchored by high-floor, high-ceiling plays today, headlined by **Jackson Merrill** (74.69) and **Gunnar Henderson** (74.65). **Jackson Merrill** benefits significantly from his leadoff spot and a favorable matchup against Taillon, while **Gunnar Henderson** exploits a massive park factor boost (+16%) and a strong platoon edge against Lambert. **Kyle Tucker** (73.24) and **Jacob Wilson** (72.74) also profile as elite starts; **Jacob Wilson** particularly benefits from a +10% boost for hitting at the top of the order, while **Josh Lowe** (72.21) remains a tactical necessity. Though **Josh Lowe** faces Fedde, his +19% SP skill advantage and high stolen base probability make him an essential engine for our league-leading speed requirements, despite the modest raw base projection.\n\nOur most significant narrative today is the optimization of our outfield and utility slots. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (78.22) is our strongest overall play, buoyed by a substantial BvP historical edge (+8%) against Bello and solid xwOBA metrics. While **Marcell Ozuna** (61.53) gets the nod in the utility slot due to wind conditions favoring a higher launch angle, **Josh Jung** (54.61) was the final player left on the cutting room floor. Ultimately, the optimizer prioritized the higher efficiency and batting order stability of our starters over **Josh Jung**, whose marginal score didn't quite clear the threshold to displace our current roster construction. \n\nRisk management remains a priority given that several of our starters, including **Drake Baldwin**, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Jacob Wilson**, **Gunnar Henderson**, and **Marcell Ozuna**, are currently listed with pending lineups. **Drake Baldwin** faces the toughest test of the day against the elite arm of Skubal (2.71 xERA), which suppresses his score to a marginal 47.27. Meanwhile, we are monitoring the bench closely; **Heliot Ramos** (42.36) remains benched not just due to score, but due to a 40% rain risk in his contest against Sanchez. We are prioritizing reliable plate appearances today to maximize our efficiency metrics while maintaining the aggressive speed-focused approach that defines the Austin Waves.",
